.Dd November 21, 2024
.Dt GCORE-INTERNAL 1
.Os Darwin
.Sh NAME
.Nm gcore
.Nd get core images of running processes and corpses
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl q
.Op Fl C
.Op Fl S
.Op Fl g
.Op Fl d
.Op Fl N
.Op Fl f Ar outfd
.Op Fl t Ar threshold
.Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
For an introduction to this command and its options, see
.Xr gcore 1 .
This page describes various experimental capabilities
of the
.Nm
command intended, for Apple Internal use only.
.Pp
The following set of additional flags are available:
.Bl -tag -width Fl
.It Fl N
Add virtual memory metadata to the core file for consumption
by internal memory tools.
.It Fl g
Stream the core file content through an invocation of
.Xr gzip 1 ,
writing the gzip-compressed content to the destination file.
The resulting core file should be uncompressed with
.Xr gunzip 1
.Em before
attempting to examine it with, for example,
.Xr otool 1
or
.Xr lldb 1 .
Some content restrictions apply!
.It Fl q
Errors and faults are always logged, but this option prevents them from
also being printed on stderr.
.It Fl f Ar outfd
Use
.Ar outfd
as the file descriptor to write the core file to.
.El
.Pp
The remaining options are more relevant to the
.Nm
maintainers:
.Bl -tag -width Fl
.It Fl C
Forcibly generate a corpse for the process, even if the process is suspended.
.It Fl t Ar threshold
Set the threshold at which I/O caching is disabled to
.Ar threshold
KiBytes.
.It Fl S
Write the core file using only streaming operations (needed for the
.Fl g
option).
.It Fl d
Enable debugging of the
.Nm
command.
Repeated flags means more information is printed.
.El
.Pp
If the
.Ar pid
value is specified as 0,
.Nm
assumes it has been passed a corpse (mach) port by its parent;
if so it will generate a core dump for that corpse.
The
.Fl c
flag may not be used in this case, as the process context may no longer exist.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr gzip 1 ,
.Xr gunzip 1 .
.Sh ISSUES
Streaming mode is incomplete.
For example, the various LC_NOTE segments that provide additional
information to debuggers about the dump are not written out
in streaming mode.
